Package fr.iutvalence.info.but.r2_01.labyrinthGame.core

Class Labyrinth

java.lang.Object
fr.iutvalence.info.but.r2_01.labyrinthGame.core.Labyrinth
public class Labyrinth extends Object
Class representing a labyrinth. A labyrinth is a 2D grid of cells, including a spawn and an exit. A labyrinth is defined by forbidden cells (surrounded by walls) positions, width/height and spawn/exit positions.

  • Constructor Details

    • Labyrinth

      public Labyrinth(int theWidth, int theHeight, Position[] theForbiddenCellPositions, Position theSpawnPosition, Position theExitPosition) throws InvalidLabyrinthException
      Returns a new labyrinth with given size, exit/spawn and forbidden cell positions.
      Parameters:
      theWidth - width
      theHeight - height
      theForbiddenCellPositions - forbidden cells positions
      theSpawnPosition - spawn position
      theExitPosition - exit position
      Throws:
      InvalidLabyrinthException - if labyrinth parameters are invalid: 
           - size is invalid
     - spawn or exit positions are out of bounds
     - spawn and exit positions are the same
     - spawn or exit positions are the same as a wall
